        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A five-minute bedtime tapping practice from Day 29 of a 30-day sleep programme. The night tap for Day 29 works through the habit of checking and controlling at bedtime, monitoring the body for signs of failure, rehearsing bad nights before they happen. The script moves through forgiveness of the struggle and arrives at a full surrender: body and mind wanting exactly the same thing, and agreeing to stop fighting it.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "New to tapping? Read ",
